item.title: Need help with my Java
item.dc:creator: @V113 V1
item.description:
@V113 wrote:

by open do you mean run.bat? … if you cannot open ANY server it will be your JRE. If you cannot run any server it will be your JDK.

go to my computer > program files > java - here you will see which JDK you have, simply right click the run.bat and select edit. Edit the text that looks something along the lines of 1.6.0_28 … if that’s not the problem then it’s your JRE, simply go to oracles site and download another.

  • btw, wrong section haha
